The second layer is a single yellow block (index 6) positioned on top of, and centered between, the two green blocks. The top layer contains a vertical orange block (index 10) sitting atop the yellow block, and finally a yellow semi-circular block (index 15) on top of the orange block.

**3. Determine the Assembly Order:**

```json
{
  "Step1": "Move block with index 1",
  "Step2": "Move block with index 1",
  "Step3": "Move block with index 6",
  "Step4": "Move block with index 10",
```

Therefore, the assembly starts by placing the two green blocks (index 1) in the bottom layer, then the yellow block (index 6) on top, followed by the orange block (index 10), and lastly the yellow semi-circular block (index 15) to complete the structure.
